{
  "texts": [
    "Since 2017, 69 countries have collectively adopted over 800 AI regulations (World Health Organization, 2018).",
    "Regulations aim to address issues such as bias, discrimination, privacy, and security.",
    "Most regulatory frameworks seek to foster AI development while safeguarding individual rights and societal interests as well as fighting disinformation.",
    "Some regulations, like the EU AI Act, will apply to AI systems used within their jurisdiction, regardless of the provider's location (European Parliament, 2022).",
    "The EU's artificial intelligence act is a comprehensive risk-based framework that categorizes AI applications by risk level."
  ]
}